    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"498029\">Andreas Hindborg</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/A.20.60AlwaysZero.60.20type.20for.20padding.3F/near/570634961\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I don't understand when you would need this?  How does it help the flag situation over having just a u32?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>When you also wants to get mutable reference to the <code>bool</code> in it, when possible: <a href=\"http://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20260128115200.3820113-1-tomo@aliasing.net/\">http://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20260128115200.3820113-1-tomo@aliasing.net/</a></p>",
        "id": 570635187,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1769625775
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>you could just cast the pointer and have an invariant on the value?</p>",
        "id": 570635277,
